VarAttributes.CATDESC: EFW Boom Electronics Board (BEB) configuration code (on-board sensor biases
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Indicates the configuration of the EFW Boom Electronics Board (BEB).  Encodes the following information:  for each sensor, sensor current bias, usher and guard voltage bias.  See EFW-FAQ (http://rbsp.space.umn.edu/efw_faq.html) for a detailed description of the mapping between code value and instrument configuration (not crucial for L2 data interpretation)..

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> EFW Digital Fields Board (DFB) Configuration code (on-board spectral and waveform processing configuration)
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Indicates the configuration of the EFW Digital Filter Board (DFB).  Encodes the following information:  assignment of analog input channels to the various on-board spectral processors (FBK, SPEC, XSPEC); parameters of the on-board B-field-aligned data processing; nominal or contingency multiplexer programming.  See EFW-FAQ (http://rbsp.space.umn.edu/efw_faq.html) for a detailed description of the mapping from code value to instrument configuration (not crucial for L2 data interpretation)..

VarAttributes.CATDESC: The maximum magnitude of the sensor potential relative to SC potential at which the sensor preamp likely to be saturated during nominal biasing conditions.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: If the magnitude of a given sensor potential exceeds vsvy_maxval then the corresponding element of efw_qual (v1_saturation .. v6-saturation) shall be set to indicate that state.  vsvy_maxval is set in the L1>L2 processing scripts, and shall be copied into this variable during L2 CDF creation.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: The maximum magnitude of any component of the E-field estimate at which one could expect instrumental effects to dominate, rather than geophysical fields.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: If the magnitude of an component of the spinfit E_field estimate exceeds e_maxval then the corresponding element of efw_qual (e_magnitude shall be set to indicate that state.  e_maxval is set in the L1>L2 processing scripts, and shall be copied into this variable during L2 CDF creation.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: The maximum magnitude of the parallel component of E at which one could expect instrumental effects to dominate, rather than geophysical fields.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: If the magnitude of the parallel (to local B) component of the spinfit E-field estimate exceeds epara_maxval then the corresponding element of efw_qual (epara_magnitude) shall be set to indicate that state.  epara_maxval is set in the L1>L2 processing scripts, and shall be copied into this variable during L2 CDF creation.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: EFW_QUAL_GOOD is the value of an element of efw_qual that indicates good data.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: EFW_QUAL_GOOD is the value (typ. 0) an element of efw_qual takes when the data quality is determined to be good according to that criterion.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: EFW_QUAL_UNK is the value of an element of efw_qual that indicates the quality is unknown.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: EFW_QUAL_UNK is the value (typ. -1) an element of efw_qual takes when the data quality is determined to be good according to that criterion.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: EFW_QUAL_NR is the value of an element of efw_qual that indicates that that particular element of efw_qual is not relevant for the given data product..
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: EFW_QUAL_NR is the value (typ. -2) an element of efw_qual takes when the criterion represented by that element is not relevant for the given data product.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: See the EFW-FAQ (http://rbsp.space.umn.edu/efw_faq.html) for detailed description of the determination and meaning of each of the elements of efw_qual.

An array that indicates a global estimate of EFW data quality, as well as a breakdown of observatory and instrument-level data quality issues that impact the global quality estimate..
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: The quality of EFW data products can be affected by a variety of observatory and instrument-level conditions.  efw_qual is a collection of flags that show the estimate of each of these contributors over time.  ..See the EFW-FAQ (http://rbsp.space.umn.edu/efw_faq.html) for a detailed description of the determination and meaning of each of the elements of efw_qual...If the value of a particular element of efw_qual is not relevant to the quality of a particular data product, it shall receive the value EFW_QUAL_NR (typ. -2)...If the value of a particular element of efw_qual is relevant to the quality of a particular data product but is not known at the time lf L2 data production, it shall receive the value EFW_QUAL_DUNNO (typ. -1)...A quality value of EFW_QUAL_GOOD (typ. 0) indicates that there are no known issues with the data product due to that particular element of efw_qual...The quality values are meant to be conservative, and values other than EFW_QUAL_GOOD should lead the user back to a member of the EFW instrument team for discussion and advice on the nature of the data quality as needed.
